Fresh Pi session: SELECT EXACTLY ONE CANON TDD SCENARIO.

Inputs:
- Approved use case: latest file under {{run.dir}}/use-case/
- Test-list history: {{run.dir}}/test-list/scenarios-initial.json and any scenarios-*.json snapshots
- Repository constraints: {{run.dir}}/design/repository-constraints.md
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}
- Issues, if any: {{run.issues-file}}

Goal:
Select one pending behavioral scenario whose concrete test should be written next.

Rules:
- Read the newest valid test-list snapshot; use the initial list when no update exists.
- Select exactly one pending scenario. Test order is a design decision: prefer the smallest scenario likely to provide useful interface feedback and meaningful red against current behavior.
- Do not select an already-satisfied scenario on the theory that its test can be made red by adding a different pending scenario as a negative control.
- Do not edit repository files or the test list.
- Do not design implementation or write a test.
- If no pending scenarios remain, write an empty scenario object and status `no_actions`.
- Otherwise copy the selected scenario exactly and use status `actions_needed`.

Write:
- Selected scenario: {{run.dir}}/tdd/current-scenario-{{run.round}}.json
- Selection rationale: {{run.dir}}/tdd/selection-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/tdd/select-status-{{run.round}}.json

Status examples:
{"status":"actions_needed","summary":"selected SC-001","issues_file":null}
{"status":"no_actions","summary":"test list is empty","issues_file":null}
